---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="FAQ" 
  description="Frequently asked questions about Japanese landscaping, Ueki services, Bonsai care, and our design process."
>
  <!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero" style="background-image: url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1519552928909-5ca50ae0d54d?w=1920&q=80');">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
      <p>Find answers to common questions about our services</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Content -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="faq-layout">
        <!-- Services & Consultation -->
        <div class="faq-section">
          <h2>Services & Consultation</h2>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What services do you offer?</h3>
            <p>We specialize in three main areas:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Ueki Services:</strong> Traditional Japanese garden tree care, including selection, placement, pruning (Niwaki), and maintenance</li>
              <li><strong>Bonsai Services:</strong> Custom Bonsai creation, styling, maintenance, and consultation</li>
              <li><strong>Landscape Design:</strong> Complete Japanese garden design, installation, and project management</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Do you offer consultations?</h3>
            <p>Yes! We offer initial consultations to discuss your vision, assess your space, and provide recommendations. The consultation fee is applied toward any design or installation services you book.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What areas do you serve?</h3>
            <p>We primarily serve the Portland metro area and surrounding regions including Eugene, Salem, and Vancouver, WA. For larger projects, we may be able to travel further - please inquire.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>How much does a typical project cost?</h3>
            <p>Projects vary widely based on scope, size, and materials. A small consultation might be a few hundred dollars, while a complete garden redesign can range from $10,000 to $50,000+. We're happy to provide estimates during the consultation phase.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Design & Installation -->
        <div class="faq-section">
          <h2>Design & Installation</h2>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>How long does a typical project take?</h3>
            <p>Timeline depends on the project scope:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Small pruning projects: 1 day</li>
              <li>Courtyard gardens: 2-4 weeks</li>
              <li>Full landscape redesigns: 6-12 weeks</li>
              <li>Ongoing maintenance: Seasonal visits throughout the year</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Can you work with my existing landscape?</h3>
            <p>Absolutely! Many of our projects involve enhancing or transforming existing landscapes. We can work with mature trees, existing hardscaping, and integrate new elements harmoniously.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Do you source all materials?</h3>
            <p>Yes, we handle all plant procurement, materials sourcing, and delivery. We have relationships with specialty nurseries for authentic Japanese plants and materials.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Will the plants survive our climate?</h3>
            <p>Yes! We carefully select species that thrive in the Pacific Northwest climate while maintaining authentic Japanese garden aesthetics. We choose plants hardy to our zone and suited to your specific site conditions.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Maintenance & Care -->
        <div class="faq-section">
          <h2>Maintenance & Care</h2>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Do you offer ongoing maintenance?</h3>
            <p>Yes, we offer seasonal maintenance plans that include pruning, fertilizing, pest management, and general care. This ensures your garden remains healthy and beautiful year-round.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>How often do Japanese garden trees need pruning?</h3>
            <p>Most Ueki (Japanese garden trees) benefit from pruning once or twice per year:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Pines:</strong> Late autumn after growth hardens</li>
              <li><strong>Maples:</strong> Winter dormancy and summer touch-ups</li>
              <li><strong>Flowering trees:</strong> After blooming</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Can you train me to maintain my own garden?</h3>
            <p>Yes! We offer maintenance training sessions where we teach you the basics of Japanese garden care, including proper pruning techniques, seasonal tasks, and species-specific care.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What if something dies or doesn't thrive?</h3>
            <p>We stand behind our work. If a plant fails to thrive due to installation issues within the first year, we'll work with you to address the problem. All plants come with a one-year warranty (excluding damage from neglect, weather extremes, or pests).</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Bonsai Specific -->
        <div class="faq-section">
          <h2>Bonsai Specific</h2>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Do you sell Bonsai trees?</h3>
            <p>We occasionally have Bonsai available for sale, and we can source specific species upon request. We also create custom Bonsai from nursery stock or collected material.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>How often does Bonsai need maintenance?</h3>
            <p>Active maintenance (watering, feeding) is daily to weekly depending on season and species. Structural work (pruning, wiring, repotting) is seasonal - typically 2-4 times per year. We offer maintenance services if you prefer professional care.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Can you work on my existing Bonsai?</h3>
            <p>Yes! We offer styling, repotting, pest management, and general health consultations for existing Bonsai collections.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What species do you recommend for beginners?</h3>
            <p>For the Pacific Northwest, we recommend:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Japanese Maple (Acer palmatum)</li>
              <li>Trident Maple (Acer buergerianum)</li>
              <li>Japanese Black Pine (Pinus thunbergii)</li>
              <li>Juniper (Juniperus species)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>These are forgiving, readily available, and beautiful in our climate.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Getting Started -->
        <div class="faq-section">
          <h2>Getting Started</h2>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>How do I schedule a consultation?</h3>
            <p>Contact us via phone, email, or the contact form on this website. We'll schedule a convenient time to visit your site or discuss your project by phone.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What should I prepare for the consultation?</h3>
            <p>Consider your goals, budget, and timeline. Photos of your space are helpful. If you have inspiration images (gardens, specific plants, design elements), please share those as well.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Do you have a portfolio I can review?</h3>
            <p>Yes! Please visit our <a href="/portfolio">Portfolio page</a> to see completed projects. We're also happy to provide references from past clients.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What's the next step after consultation?</h3>
            <p>If we're a good fit, we'll create a detailed proposal including design concepts, plant selections, timeline, and pricing. Once approved, we'll schedule the work and begin transforming your space.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <h2>Still Have Questions?</h2>
      <p>We're happy to answer any questions not covered here. Please don't hesitate to reach out.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top: var(--spacing-md);">Contact Us</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    height: 50vh;
    min-height: 400px;
  }
  
  .faq-layout {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  
  .faq-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xxl);
  }
  
  .faq-section:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  
  .faq-section > h2 {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    border-bottom: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
  }
  
  .faq-item {
    background-color: var(--color-white);
    padding: var(--spacing-md);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  }
  
  .faq-item h3 {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-size: 20px;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }
  
  .faq-item p {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }
  
  .faq-item p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  
  .faq-item ul {
    margin: var(--spacing-sm) 0;
    padding-left: var(--spacing-md);
  }
  
  .faq-item li {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
  }
  
  .faq-item a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  
  .cta-section {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary) 0%, #1e3829 100%);
    color: var(--color-white);
    padding: var(--spacing-xl) 0;
  }
  
  .cta-section h2 {
    color: var(--color-white);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }
  
  .cta-section p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-quote);
  }
</style>

